Yes, I checked the room schedule and the smaller table should fit by the window if we move the plant first.
For lunch, a simple soup and bread plan sounds easier because people may arrive at different times.
I can bring plates, and Sam said he would handle tea.
If the meeting runs long, we can pause after the second topic and finish the list on Thursday.
Also, the notes do not need formal wording yet, just the main decisions and who is handling each step.

BlueCross BlueShield

2026 member coverage update

 

Important information about your 2026 plan updates

There are changes to your coverage plan for 2026, and residents in your area may also receive a Medicare Kit provided at no charge.

Your plan includes coverage selections that need to be reviewed for 2026. Alongside those updates, this Medicare Kit is being made available to qualifying households in your area. The kit is provided at no charge, you will not be billed for the kit, and there is a limit of one per household. Total program allocation is 800 kits. Availability ends tomorrow.

View kit and 2026 details

What your package includes

The enclosed materials are intended to support everyday care needs and provide a convenient summary of upcoming plan changes for 2026.

Adhesive bandages assortment

Digital oral thermometer

Antiseptic cleansing wipes

Reusable pill organizer

Disposable face masks

Non-latex exam gloves

Hot and cold therapy pack

2026 coverage change summary booklet

Quantities are determined by program allocation and household eligibility.

Please note that the kit is separate from your coverage choices, but both are being shared together so you have one clear place to review what is included. The mailing is intended for Medicare-eligible residents in the service area, with one kit per household at no charge.

Thank you for being part of BlueCross BlueShield. We appreciate the opportunity to keep you informed.

 

About the garden question, I think the shorter stakes will work better because the wind has been calmer near the back fence.
You asked whether we should plant everything this week, and I would split it into two mornings so the soil can settle after watering.
The basil can stay in smaller pots for a bit longer.
If Maya joins on Sunday, she can handle labels while I bring the twine and notebook.
That should keep the plan simple and easier to adjust later.

